{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AzarRAMPGBPEX9A84eRtqF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here's a detailed understanding of the key components:\n\n### 1. **RunStore Interface and Implementations**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n\nThe `RunStore` interface defines the contract for run persistence:\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n\tCreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n\tGetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n\tUpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n\tDeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n\tListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n\tListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n\tListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n}\n```\n\n**SQLite Implementation:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n- Uses `modernc.org/sqlite` with WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) mode for concurrent access\n- Tables: `runs`, `step_executions`, `log_files`, `merge_queue`, `evolution_log`\n- Key columns tracked: `id`, `workflow_name`, `state`, `active_steps`, `started_at`, `completed_at`, `project_dir`, `error_message`, `container_id`, `base_sha`, `container_kept`, `title`\n- Supports batch filtering by project and timestamp filtering for listing historical runs\n\n### 2. **Domain Types**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/`\n\n**Run** (`run.go`):\n- States: `pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`\n- Tracks: ID, workflow name, state, active steps, step executions, timestamps, project directory, error messages, container ID, base SHA (for branch creation), title\n- Methods: `Start()`, `RecordStepStart()`, `RecordStepComplete()`, `Complete()`, `Fail()`\n\n**Workflow** (`workflow.go`):\n- Locations: `container` or `host`\n- Components: steps (map), wiring (directed graph), collects (synchronization), entry step, config\n- Validation: checks reachability, wiring completeness, config keys, location constraints\n\n**Step**:\n- Types: `agent`, `script`, `workflow`\n- Contains: name, type, declared results, config map\n- Config keys: `prompt`, `run`, `max_attempts`, `timeout`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `workflow_name`, `prompt_step`, etc.\n\n### 3. **Host Workflow Executor**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/`\n\n**Runner** (`runner.go`):\n- Reads `.cloche/host.cloche` and executes the `main` workflow\n- Uses the `Engine` for step graph traversal\n- Generates unique run IDs for orchestration\n- Creates output directory: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n- Returns: `RunResult` with run ID and final state\n\n**Executor** (`executor.go`):\n- Implements `engine.StepExecutor` interface\n- Two step types:\n  1. **Script steps** (`executeScript`): runs shell commands on host with environment variables\n  2. **Workflow steps** (`executeWorkflow`): dispatches container runs via `RunDispatcher` (gRPC)\n- Handles output mapping: evaluates JSON paths from wired step outputs and passes as environment variables\n- **Polling mechanism**: `waitForRun()` polls RunStore every 2 seconds until container run reaches terminal state\n- **Direct RunStore interaction**: calls `Store.GetRun()` to check status during polling\n\n### 4. **CLI Commands**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/`\n\n**Main commands:**\n- `cloche run --workflow <name>` → calls `RunWorkflow` RPC\n- `cloche status <run-id>` → calls `GetStatus` RPC\n- `cloche logs <run-id>` → calls `StreamLogs` RPC (with optional filtering)\n- `cloche poll <run-id>` → (`poll.go`) polls `GetStatus` every 2 seconds, watches for terminal states\n- `cloche list [--all]` → calls `ListRuns` RPC (filters to last hour by default)\n- `cloche stop <run-id>` → calls `StopRun` RPC\n- `cloche delete <id>` → calls `DeleteContainer` RPC\n- `cloche orchestrate` → calls `Orchestrate` RPC (now returns error: \"orchestrator has been removed; use host workflow instead\")\n\n### 5. **Web Portal Handlers**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nRoutes served:\n- `GET /` → project overview\n- `GET /projects/{name}/runs` → project-specific run list\n- `GET /runs` → all runs list\n- `GET /runs/{id}` → run detail page\n- `GET /projects/{name}` → project detail\n- API endpoints:\n  - `GET /api/projects` → list all projects\n  - `GET /api/runs` → list runs (JSON)\n  - `GET /api/runs/{id}` → run detail (JSON)\n  - `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` → step output\n  - `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` → SSE stream for live logs\n  - `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` → delete retained container\n\n### 6. **gRPC Service Definitions**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` & generated code in `/workspace/api/clochepb/`\n\n**Current Service (ClocheService):**\n```\nrpc RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) returns (RunWorkflowResponse)\nrpc GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) returns (GetStatusResponse)\nrpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry)\nrpc StopRun(StopRunRequest) returns (StopRunResponse)\nrpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse)\nrpc Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) returns (ShutdownResponse)\nrpc DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) returns (DeleteContainerResponse)\n```\n\n**Note on Orchestrate:** The `Orchestrate(OrchestrateRequest) → OrchestrateResponse` RPC exists in generated gRPC bindings but has been removed from the proto file. The implementation in `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (line 667) returns an error: \"orchestrator has been removed; use host workflow instead\"\n\n### 7. **Daemon (cloched) Architecture**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\nFlow:\n1. Initializes SQLite store\n2. Marks stale runs (pending/running from crashed daemon) as failed\n3. Initializes container runtime (Docker or Local)\n4. Creates gRPC and HTTP servers\n5. **Auto-runs active projects**: scans `ListProjects()`, reads project config, finds projects with `active=true`, spawns `Runner` goroutines\n6. Listens on gRPC socket and HTTP port\n\n**Key integration point with RunStore:**\n- `launchAndTrack()` goroutine created per container run\n- Updates RunStore as container produces status messages (step started/completed)\n- Polls container until exit, then extracts outputs and marks run complete\n\n### 8. **Key Data Flow for Container Runs**\n\n1. **RPC Call** → `RunWorkflow()` creates `Run` in store (state: `pending`)\n2. **Background Launch** → `launchAndTrack()` starts container, updates `Run` state to `running`\n3. **Tracking** → parses JSON-line status messages from container, calls `UpdateRun()` for each step event\n4. **Completion** → container exits, branch extraction happens, final state persisted\n5. **Access** → CLI/web portal queries via `GetRun()`, `ListRuns()`, or `GetCaptures()`\n\n### 9. **Host Workflow Integration with RunStore**\n\nThe host executor directly uses RunStore to:\n- Poll container run status: `Store.GetRun(ctx, runID)` in `waitForRun()` loop\n- Determine when dispatched container workflow completes before proceeding to next host step\n- No creation/update of host-level runs in current implementation (host runs are logged but not persisted as Run objects)\n\n### 10. **Run Tracking Tables & Schema**\n\n**Primary:** `runs` table (id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept, title)\n\n**Supporting:**\n- `step_executions` (for detailed step tracking, indexed by run_id)\n- `log_files` (extracted logs indexed by run_id, step_name, file_type)\n- `evolution_log` (tracks code generation history)\n- `merge_queue` (for merged results coordination)\n\nAll relevant absolute file paths are:\n- `